cp.diachronicDesc: Corpora used to study changes in time using the Trends feature. Diachronic corpora contain time information about when a text was published or used.
cp.error-annotatedDesc: Corpora used to study errors produced by users of the language: typically learner's errors or translator's errors. The corpora contain error annotation giving details about the error, correction and type of error.
cp.featuredDesc: Manually selected high-quality general-purpose corpora. A recommended starting point for new users.
cp.generalDesc: Corpora recommended for general use. They contain a large variety of language and are best to look for information about how language is used in general.
cp.gramdevDesc: Corpora used when developing word sketch grammars.

cp.learnerDesc: Corpora used to study language produced by learners. It is typically used to study learner's errors. A learner corpus may or may not be error-annotated.

cp.openCorporaNote: Subscribe to get access to hundreds of corpora in 90+ languages.
cp.parallelDesc: Corpora used to search for translations or to study them. A parallel corpus consists of two or more monolingual corpora which are translations of one another and whose corresponding segments (sentences or paragraphs) are aligned (matched).

cp.spokenDesc: Corpora used to study spoken language. They are made up of transcripts of spoken language.
cp.webDesc: Corpora created mainly from texts intended for publication on the web. Downloading material from the web is the only viable option to create the largest multi-billion word corpora.
